OL,3,CTrain crash passenger saw 'bloodied
OL,4,Cfaces' and people 'in a very bad way'
OL,6,FA passenger on one of the trains
OL,7,Finvolved in the crash said he saw
OL,8,Fpeople in a "very bad way" after the
OL,9,Fcollision
OL,11,FA passenger has described "faces all
OL,12,Fbloodied" and seeing some people "in a
OL,13,Fvery bad way" after a train collided
OL,14,Fwith another near Bedford on Friday
OL,15,Fevening.
OL,17,FSpeaking to ITV News, Peter Knapp said
OL,18,Fthat soon after he boarded the train,
OL,19,Fhe witnessed "a sudden explosion of
OL,20,Fmist" and hit his head on the seat in
OL,21,Ffront of him.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
